Oooh, I like your idea of incorporating opera and wildlife-themed trivia questions, John! I'm sure everyone will enjoy singing those Italian songs during our hikes. I'm also looking forward to sharing some of my favorite Italian films, like Il Postino and Nuovo Cinema Paradiso, with all of you! Who knows, we might even come up with a new post-hike tradition (;

And John, about the wildlife trivia questions you've thought of, I think it's important to add some variety, just like we're doing with our movie selections. I also think it would be interesting to guess the ARP for a wildlife tour guide in the Italian Alps during our hikes. Let me know if you have any more ideas on this!

Talking about wildlife, did you know that there are over 5,000 species of wild mammals in Italy? Some of my favorites are the Italian brown bear and the Marsican brown bear. I'd love to hear what kinds of wildlife everyone hopes to see during our hikes, too!
